The President of the United States is celebrating the 244th birthday of the United States Army. He praises the Army for its dedication to duty, honor, and discipline, and for its role in defending national security both at home and abroad. He also highlights the Army's instrumental role in the success of Operation Overlord during World War II and its ongoing commitment to protecting freedom. The President expresses gratitude to current and former soldiers for their resolve, defense of values, and love of country. He concludes by asking for God's protection and blessings for the Armed Forces and the United States.